JMC Notes 0623

- Javascript!!!!!
- "Inifinite scroll".  Does refreshes when you reach the bottom of a page.  
  Content isn't hidden; doesn't exist.  Uses AJAX
- Trello.com website
- http://physicsketch.appspot.com.  Open canvas that has physics properties applied.  super cool
- Question: element:hover versus javascript onclick?
- Put <script> tags towards end of body section.  Otherwise, script will load before
  content
- javascript: multiple spaces are ignored
- metaraine.github.io/gettingStartedJS/#/4
- javascript types: 5 primitive types aka "builtin types"
  - string
  - number
  - boolean
  - null.  useful for knowing a var is set but is blank.
  - undefined.  var defs w/o values are set to this.  can assign the value

- javascript types: non-primitive types
  - arrays: arr.reverse(), arr.push('new') returns new length, arr.pop() removes last item
  - arrays: arr.unshift('new') adds to beginning of list, arr.shift() removes first item 
  - arrays: arr.sort(), arr.slice(starting index,end index not including last)
  - arrays: some methods/functions have 'side effects'.  reverse() modifies original, slice 
    does not
  - arrays: arr.join(', ') combines list into single, double quoted one

- javascript types: objects
  - "key value pair"  -> "var array = {key1:"value1",key2:"value2"}"
  - arrays have numeric indices, objects have string indices!
  - objects values can be null and/or undefined
  - Example:
    	var cat = {
    		name: 'Garfield',
    		colors: ['orange', 'white']
    	}
    	cat['colors'].length
    	cat['colors'][0] (bracket notation for individual color)
  - "dot notation".  valid identifier, no spaces, doesn't start with #, no dashes
  - "dot notation".  cat['name'] = cat.name
  - "delete cat['name']" removes property value pair
  - As long as it's valid identifier, can add/remove/etc with both bracket and dot notations
  - "Object.keys(<objectname>)" returns all the key values
  - Object properties(name, color, age, etc) are unordered.
